data.title: "Landline" Episode #9.20 (TV Episode 2000)
data.meta_description: Episode #9.20: With Anne Kruger, Ian Henschke. Australian farmers are cashing in on the growing overseas demand for organic produce. With buyers paying up to 30 per cent more for chemical-free produce, the financial incentives are becoming more and more attractive for farmers to go organic. And while the burgeoning demand is boosting the bottom line for growers, the move towards organic agriculture is helping to make farming practices in Australia more sustainable.
